      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1775674200873,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "here is the complete guid about the info u have to\nput:\n\n1) Name of instance\n2) u have to select the OS u wants on  your Vm like\nUbuntu , redhat etc\n3 next u have to select the instance type as per ur\nrequirement . like micro nano.....\n4) key pair to connect to ur VM. but now i u can\nleave as it is. beacuse i think AWS lets u to\nconnect to ur VM\n5)network setting: this was called firewall rule of ur\nVM/. but for now i am going with http trafic\n6) lastly  u have to choose the space u want.\n6) then click to launch the instance",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "here is the complete guid about the info u have to put:\n\n1) Name of instance\n2) u have to select the OS u wants on  your Vm like Ubuntu , redhat etc\n3 next u have to select the instance type as per ur requirement . like micro nano.....\n4) key pair to connect to ur VM. but now i u can leave as it is. beacuse i think AWS lets u to connect to ur VM\n5)network setting: this was called firewall rule of ur VM/. but for now i am going with http trafic\n6) lastly  u have to choose the space u want.\n6) then click to launch the instance",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
